## 1. Activator.getDefault() — What it returns and when it's safe

**File:** `/work/data/repos/eclipse-wildwebdeveloper__wildwebdeveloper/org.eclipse.wildwebdeveloper.xml/src/org/eclipse/wildwebdeveloper/xml/internal/Activator.java`

```java
public class Activator extends AbstractUIPlugin {
    private static Activator plugin;

    @Override
    public void start(BundleContext context) throws Exception {
        super.start(context);
        plugin = this;  // <-- set here
    }

    @Override
    public void stop(BundleContext context) throws Exception {
        plugin = null;  // <-- cleared here
        super.stop(context);
    }

    public static Activator getDefault() {
        return plugin;
    }
}
```

**Key finding:** `getDefault()` returns a `private static Activator plugin` field that is only set during `start()` and cleared during `stop()`. Calling `getDefault()` **before** the bundle is activated returns `null`, which would cause a `NullPointerException` if dereferenced.

